# Build context for apps/umi-api/Dockerfile is the REPO ROOT. Drop everything
# heavy, secret, or unrelated to the umi-api image so the daemon context stays
# small and no .env / other-app payload is ever sent. The Dockerfile COPYs only
# the manifests + apps/umi-api source it needs.
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/coverage
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/*.log

# Never ship secrets.
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# VCS / CI / docs / local tooling — not build inputs.
.git
.github
.hermes
docs
backups
artifacts

# Other apps are not needed to build umi-api (umi-cash is workspace-excluded;
# umi-kds is a native app). Their package.json isn't a workspace member, so
# dropping them entirely keeps the context lean.
apps/umi-cash
apps/umi-kds
